<!-- Game Description Table -->

<table class="tablestyle" id="table14" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="0">
	<tr>
		<td class="sectional">

<!-- Game Description Header -->
		
		<table class="headertable" id="table15" cellspacing="2" cellpadding="2">
			<tr>
				<td class="headercell">
				<img border="0" src="../../../images/headers/gamedes.jpg" width="240" height="33"></td>
			</tr>
		</table>

<!-- Game Description Sectional -->

<table border="0" width="100%" id="table16" cellpadding="0">
	<tr>
		<td style="font-family: Trebuchet MS; font-size: 8pt; color: #FFFFFF; font-weight: bold; text-align: left; background-color: #333333; border-left: 2px solid #000000; border-right: 2px solid #FFFFFF; border-top: 2px solid #000000; border-bottom: 2px solid #FFFFFF">
			<br>Crazy Climber is a coin-operated arcade game produced by Nichibutsu in 1980. It was also released in North America by Taito America Corporation by UA Ltd. in 1982 for the Emerson Arcadia 2001 and other video game consoles. It is one of Nichibutsu's most highly-acclaimed video games in its library. A precursor to the platform game genre, Crazy Climber was the first game revolving around climbing, specifically climbing buildings, before Nintendo's 1981 release Donkey Kong.
                  <br><br>In Crazy Climber the player assumes the role of a daredevil who is attempting to climb to the top of four skyscrapers. There are a number of obstacles and dangers to avoid including:
                  <br><br>- Windows that open and close (the most common danger).
                  <br>- Bald-headed residents (a.k.a. Mad Doctors), who throw objects such as flower pots, buckets of water and fruit in an effort to knock the climber off the building (with larger objects appearing by more aggressive Mad Doctors in later levels).
                  <br>- A giant condor, who drops eggs and excrement aimed at the climber (two at a time in the early stages, four in later levels).
                  <br>- A giant ape (styled like King Kong), whose punch can prove deadly (he becomes more aggressive in later levels).
                  <br>- Falling steel girders and iron dumbbells (more numerous in the later levels).
                  <br>- Live wires, which protrude off electric signs.
                  <br>- Falling 'Crazy Climber' signs.
                  <br><br>Some of these dangers appear at every level of the game; others make appearances only in later stages. Should the climber succumb to any one of these dangers, a new climber takes his place at the exact point where he fell; the last major danger is eliminated.
                  <br><br>One ally the climber has is a pink "Lucky Balloon"; if he is able to grab it, the climber is transported up 8 stories to a window. The window onto which it drops the climber may be about to close. If the window that the climber is dropped onto is fully closed, the balloon pauses there until the window opens up again. The player does not actually earn bonus points for catching the balloon, but he is awarded the normal 'step value' for each of the eight floors that he passes while holding the balloon.
                  <br><br>If the climber is able to ascend to the top of a skyscraper and grabs the runner of a waiting helicopter, he earns a bonus and is transported to another skyscraper, which presents more dangers than the past. The helicopter would only wait about 30 seconds, then fly off.
                  <br><br>If the player completes all four skyscrapers, he is taken back to the first skyscraper and the game restarts from the beginning, but the player keeps his score.
                  <br><br>Arcade Hits - Crazy Climber brings back the arcade classic to the Playstation console and features the original 8bit Crazy Climber and Crazy Climber '85.
                  <br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<u>Manufacturer's description:</u><br>
                  <br>Revival in Major Wave Series has emerged as the 1981 arcade game "Crazy Climber"! The stage of high-rise building, away from any interference, climbing games to escape from the top. As a character disturbance, appeared "MAN Ojama" drop, drop the droppings came from somewhere "Condor apathetic", also "King Gorilla" also fly the flag of a thing by aiming player such as an array of iron and steel "falling objects", from the window You thwart the way for the player. Includes Crazy Climber Crazy Climber & '85!
                  <br><br>You can choose from two titles of Crazy Climber Crazy Climber and '85.
                  <br>Let the top floor of the building seeks to manipulate the climber in the various techniques! Crazy Climber is a power-up '85 graphic surface. You also appeared in a number of items.
                  <br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<u>Features:</u><br>
			<ul><li>Third person perspective.</li>
			<li>2D graphics</li>
			<li>Cartoon graphics</li>
			<li>Climbing, Humour & Fantasy themes.</li></ul>
</td>

	</tr>
	</table>
	       	</td>
     </tr>
</table>  

